<h4 id="find_package">find_package</h4>

<ol>
  <li>find_package is supposed to work with Find&lt;package&gt;.cmake module</li>
  <li>The purpose of the file is to define the search rules for the package and set
different variables, such as &lt;package&gt;_FOUND, &lt;package&gt;_INCLUDE_DIRS
and &lt;package&gt;_LIBRARIES.</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="default">Default</h4>
<ol>
  <li>After you install boost, it will generate boost-related file under 
<strong>/usr/local/lib/cmake/Boost-1.72.0</strong></li>
  <li>When you write the following code in <strong>CMakeLists.txt</strong>, it will go to find
related cmake file, for example <strong>BoostConfig.cmake</strong> or  <strong>BoostConfigVersion.cmake</strong></li>
</ol>

<div class="language-cmake highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">find_package</span><span class="p">(</span>Boost 1.72.0 COMPONENTS locale<span class="p">)</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<h5 id="2self-define">2.Self-define</h5>
<ul>
  <li>CMakeLists.txt</li>
</ul>

<div class="language-cmake highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">cmake_minimum_required</span><span class="p">(</span>VERSION 3.10<span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">project</span><span class="p">(</span>hello_world<span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">set</span><span class="p">(</span>CMAKE_MODULE_PATH <span class="s2">"/Users/kismet/Documents/code/cmake_code/tutorial/CMake/Help/guide/tutorial/my_step/cmake/modules"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">find_package</span><span class="p">(</span>Opencv REQUIRED<span class="p">)</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<ul>
  <li>FindOpencv.cmake</li>
</ul>

<div class="language-cmake highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">message</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"this is find opencv"</span><span class="p">)</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

